# Create Component Procedure

1. Create component in `src/components/<domain>/<Name>.tsx`.
2. Use functional component with hooks and proper TypeScript types.
3. Add accessibility: roles, labels, keyboard focus.
4. Add test `src/components/<domain>/<Name>.test.tsx` (colocated).
5. Use Dexie for data access via `db` from `@/services/db` or `useLiveQuery`.
6. Validate props with TypeScript types and sanitize any user-provided HTML.
7. Example test skeleton:
```typescript
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import { userEvent } from '@testing-library/user-event';
import { MyComponent } from './MyComponent';

test('renders heading', () => {
  render(<MyComponent />);
  expect(screen.getByRole('heading', { name: /my component/i })).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```
